abstract: Regulators froze a Latvian account suspected of being used to hack into online brokerage accounts and manipulate stock trading.
snippet: Regulators froze a Latvian account suspected of being used to hack into online brokerage accounts and manipulate stock trading.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, March 7 (Dow Jones)  United States securities regulators obtained an emergency court order freezing $3 million of proceeds in a Latvian account suspected of being used to hack into online brokerage accounts and manipulate stock trading.

headline.main: U.S. Freezes Assets in Latvia in Stock Inquiry
headline.print_headline: U.S. Freezes Assets in Latvia In Stock Inquiry
